If anyone is looking for a solution and just want a full screen webview then you can use [platform channels](https://flutter.dev/docs/development/platform-integration/platform-channels).
I had a use case to implement oauth in my app. For this, I created a platform channel to retrieve auth code from native (Java) code like this:
**In your dart class**:
```dart
static const _authPlatform = const MethodChannel('com.example.flutter.demo/oauth');
static const _getAuthCodeMethodId = 'getAuthCode';

Future<String> _getAuthCode(String loginHint) async {
    try {
        return await _authPlatform.invokeMethod(_getAuthCodeMethodId);
    } on PlatformException {
        return null;
    }
}
```
**In MainActivity.java**:
```Java
@Override
protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
    GeneratedPluginRegistrant.registerWith(this);

    new MethodChannel(getFlutterView(), "com.example.flutter.demo/oauth").setMethodCallHandler(
            (call, result) -> {
                if ("getAuthCode".equals(call.method)) {
                    onGetAuthCodeMethodCall(call, result);
                } else {
                    result.notImplemented();
                }
            });
}

private void onGetAuthCodeMethodCall(MethodCall call, MethodChannel.Result result) {
    mGetAuthCodeResult = result;
    Intent webViewActivityIntent = new Intent(this, WebViewActivity.class);
    startActivityForResult(webViewActivityIntent, WebViewActivity.REQUEST_CODE_AUTH_CODE);
}

protected void onActivityResult(int requestCode, int resultCode, Intent data) {
    super.onActivityResult(requestCode, resultCode, data);
    mGetAuthCodeResult.success(data.getStringExtra(WebViewActivity.KEY_AUTH_CODE));
}
```
Same can be done for iOS also.

